Yobe State governor, Mai Mala Buni on Thursday met with President Muhammadu Buhari at the presidential villa to discuss issues bordering on security across the state. The governor said the meeting was imperative to strengthen security in the state as farmers approach the farming season when they are expected to cultivate their farms. Buni expressed the readiness of the state government to continue supporting security organizations in their efforts towards establishing sustainable peace and security in Yobe State. President Buhari assured that the ongoing fight against insurgency will be sustained to ensure total security in the affected states. He called on the affected state governments and people to cooperate with security agencies operating in the region. 